From Jim Eggert Subject Re Israeli destruction of mosque s in Jerusalem In article Sessions writes Or for that matter with the Around here nobody reroutes freeways to avoid churches synagogues and so They just get condemned paid off and the road goes The same is standard policy for any number of other public projects schools and sports arenas being only two Anticipating the objection that the cases aren't comparable how not The Wall has to count as the tourist attraction in that part of the world making room for the traffic would be a twenty second decision for any city council I ever heard The cases aren't really A project like a freeway requires public hearings court action appeals advance determination of restitution and so The razing of the Moghrabi district in East Jerusalem happened within hours of the end of the hostilities of the Day The residents were given only two or three hours' notice to pack up and find accomodations They had no chance of public hearing debate appeal negotiation or It was get out or die in the Jim Jim Eggert